'''Nihad Mujakić''' ({{IPA|bs|nǐxad mǔjakitɕ|pron}}; born 15 April 1998) is a Bosnian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Gaziantep F.K.|Gaziantep]], on loan from [[FK Partizan|Partizan]], and the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Mujakić started his professional career at [[FK Sarajevo|Sarajevo]], before joining [[KV Kortrijk|Kortrijk]] in 2019, who loaned him to [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] in 2020 and to [[SK Beveren|Beveren]] in 2021. The following year, he went back to Sarajevo. Later that year, he moved to [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]]. In 2024, Mujakić was transferred to Partizan, who sent him on loan to [[Eyüpspor]] in 2025 and to Gaziantep in 2026.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Mujakić made his senior international debut in 2023, earning 12 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Sarajevo===
Mujakić came through the youth academy of his hometown club [[FK Sarajevo Youth School|Sarajevo]]. In October 2015, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/premijer-liga-bih/osam-polaznika-akademije-fk-sarajevo-potpisalo-visegodisnje-ugovore-sa-prvakom-drzave-8146|title=Osam polaznika Akademije FK Sarajevo potpisalo višegodišnje ugovore sa prvakom države|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=2 October 2015|access-date=5 October 2015|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar]] on 31 July 2016 at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/sarajevo-golovima-duljevica-i-ahmetovica-slavilo-protiv-zrinjskog/160731073|title=Sarajevo golovima Duljevića i Ahmetovića slavilo protiv Zrinjskog|website=klix.ba|date=31 July 2016|access-date=1 August 2016|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2018, he extended his deal with the squad until June 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/mujakic-produzio-vjernost-sarajevu-do-2023-godine/280640|title=Mujakić produžio vjernost Sarajevu do 2023. godine|website=sportsport.ba|date=21 June 2018|access-date=23 June 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

On 19 July 2018, he scored his first professional goal in a [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|UEFA Europa League qualifier]] against [[FC Urartu|Urartu]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/sarajevo-se-rutinski-rijesilo-banantsa-ceka-se-odluka-tas-a/1170949|title=Sarajevo se rutinski riješilo Banantsa: Čeka se odluka TAS-a|website=fokus.ba|date=19 July 2018|access-date=20 July 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

He won his first trophy with the club on 15 May 2019, by beating [[NK Široki Brijeg|Široki Brijeg]] in the [[2018–19 Bosnia and Herzegovina Football Cup|Bosnian Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/fudbalski-klub-sarajevo-osvajac-kupa-bosne-i-hercegovine/336952|title=Fudbalski klub Sarajevo osvajač Kupa Bosne i Hercegovine|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=15 May 2019|access-date=15 May 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

===Kortrijk===
In January 2019, Belgian outfit [[KV Kortrijk|Kortrijk]] announced that Mujakić would join them at the end of the season on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/268453-nihad-mujakic-u-kortrijku-sarajevu-22-miliona-km|title=Nihad Mujakić u Kortrijku, Sarajevu 2,2 miliona KM|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=21 January 2019|access-date=23 January 2019|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team on 20 September against [[KV Mechelen|Mechelen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/nihad-mujakic-debitovao-za-kortrijk-u-cudnoj-utakmici/334094|title=Nihad Mujakić debitovao za Kortrijk u čudnoj utakmici|website=sportsport.ba|date=20 September 2019|access-date=20 September 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2020, he was sent on a 18-month loan to Croatian side [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/nista-od-povratka-na-kosevo-bivsi-fudbaler-sarajeva-ide-u-hrvatsku/1662654|title=Ništa od povratka na Koševo: Bivši fudbaler Sarajeva ide u Hrvatsku|website=fokus.ba|date=18 January 2020|access-date=20 January 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2021, he was loaned to [[SK Beveren|Beveren]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/nihad-mujakic-na-posudbi-u-belgijskom-drugoligasu-waasland-beverenu/210811128|title=Nihad Mujakić na posudbi u belgijskom drugoligašu Waasland-Beverenu|website=klix.ba|date=12 August 2021|access-date=15 August 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

===Return to Sarajevo===
In January 2022, Mujakić returned to Sarajevo on a deal until June 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/fk-sarajevo-ozvanicio-povratak-nihada-mujakica/444593|title=FK Sarajevo ozvaničio povratak Nihada Mujakića|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=22 January 2022|access-date=25 January 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He played his first competitive game for the club since coming back against [[FK Leotar|Leotar]] on 26 February.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/sarajevo-slavilo-u-trebinju-bez-pobjednika-u-tuzlanskom-derbiju/116549|title=Sarajevo slavilo u Trebinju, bez pobjednika u tuzlanskom derbiju|website=faktor.ba|date=26 February 2022|access-date=1 March 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

===Ankaragücü===
In August, Mujakić was transferred to Turkish team [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/fk-sarajevo-ce-dobiti-milionsko-obestecenje-nihad-mujakic-potpisao-za-ankaragucu|title=FK Sarajevo će dobiti milionsko obeštećenje: Nihad Mujakić potpisao za Ankaragücü|website=scsport.ba|date=2 August 2022|access-date=5 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted officially for the squad on 8 August against [[Konyaspor]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/763950/mujakicev-ankaragucu-protiv-sehicevog-rahmanovicevog-i-hadziahmetovicevog-konyaspora-bez-golova|title=Mujakićev Ankaragücü protiv Šehićevog, Rahmanovićevog i Hadžiahmetovićevog Konyaspora bez golova|website=avaz.ba|date=8 August 2022|access-date=10 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref> On 13 January 2024, he scored his first goal for Ankaragücü in a triumph over [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/sjajan-duel-zmajeva-u-turskoj-mujakic-zabio-prvijenac-hajradinovic-upisao-novu-asistenciju/528964|title=Sjajan duel Zmajeva u Turskoj: Mujakić zabio prvijenac, Hajradinović upisao novu asistenciju|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=13 January 2024|access-date=15 January 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

===Partizan===
In June, Mujakić moved to Serbian outfit [[FK Partizan|Partizan]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/nihad-mujakic-novi-fudbaler-partizana/191271|title=Nihad Mujakić novi fudbaler Partizana|website=faktor.ba|date=24 June 2024|access-date=25 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted competitively for the side against [[FK Napredak Kruševac|Napredak Kruševac]] on 19 July.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/433312-mujakic-debitovao-za-partizan-sok-za-dudica-na-startu-prvenstva|title=Mujakić debitovao za Partizan, šok za Dudića na startu prvenstva|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=19 July 2024|access-date=20 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2025, he was sent on a season-long loan to [[Eyüpspor]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/nihad-mujakic-je-novi-fudbaler-eyupspora|title=Nihad Mujakić je novi fudbaler Eyüpspora|website=n1info.ba|date=29 June 2025|access-date=1 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2026, he was loaned to [[Gaziantep F.K.|Gaziantep]] for the remainder of the campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/zvanicno-nihad-mujakic-predstavljen-u-novom-klubu-1106320|title=Nihad Mujakić predstavljen u novom klubu|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=17 January 2026|access-date=20 January 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Mujakić represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at various youth levels.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/867460/mujakic-sanjao-sam-da-zaigram-za-sarajevo-i-za-reprezentaciju-oboje-sam-ispunio|title=Mujakić: Sanjao sam da zaigram za Sarajevo i za reprezentaciju, oboje sam ispunio|website=avaz.ba|date=13 November 2023|access-date=15 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In November 2023, he received his first senior call up, for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] and [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/savo-milosevic-objavio-spisak-zmajeva-nekoliko-novih-imena-na-njemu|title=Savo Milošević objavio spisak Zmajeva, nekoliko novih imena na njemu|website=n1info.ba|date=2 November 2023|access-date=5 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 16 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/generacijska-sramota-tragikomicni-zmajevi-nastavili-brukati-drzavni-dres/172326|title=Generacijska sramota: Tragikomični Zmajevi nastavili brukati državni dres|website=faktor.ba|date=16 November 2023|access-date=18 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

On 6 September 2025, in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]], he scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/481613-zmajevi-razbili-san-marino-u-gostima|title=Zmajevi razbili San Marino u gostima|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=6 September 2025|access-date=9 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Mujakić was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Mujakić married his long time-girlfriend Ezgi in December 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/947183/nihad-mujakic-iskoristio-pauzu-i-u-istanbulu-ozenio-djevojku-ezgi|title=Nihad Mujakić iskoristio pauzu i u Istanbulu oženio djevojku Ezgi|website=avaz.ba|date=25 December 2024|access-date=25 December 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Ermedin Demirović]], [[Jusuf Gazibegović]], [[Haris Tabaković]], [[Haris Hajradinović]], [[Dženis Burnić]], [[Sead Kolašinac]], [[Enver Kulašin]], [[Nail Omerović]], [[Benjamin Tahirović]], [[Osman Hadžikić]] and [[Ermin Bičakčić]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Ilidža]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/prvo-dzuma-a-onda-put-za-zenicu-bh-reprezentativci-iznenadili-prisutne-u-dzamiji-na-ilidzi/483813|title=Prvo džuma, a onda put za Zenicu: Bh. reprezentativci iznenadili prisutne u džamiji na Ilidži|website=sportsport.ba|date=11 October 2024|access-date=12 October 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

